  "texts": [
    "Nonetheless, this study leaves some unanswered questions, particularly regarding the embedding of human-defined concept bottleneck models for large training datasets like ImageNet.",
    "The generation of concept subclasses using an unsupervised approach is still an open challenge that merits further investigation in order to improve the capabilities of concept bottleneck models.",
    "Furthermore, while the authors mention the possibility of incorporating human input in multimodal models, the methodology for effectively utilising expert commentary to improve concept bottleneck models is unknown.",
    "Hierarchical concept bottleneck modelsOne of the limitations of Concept Bottleneck (CB) models, as previously stated, is the requirement for critical changes to the network architecture in order to reduce the dimensions of the Bottleneck (BN) layer to match the number of concept labels.",
    "This requirement may have an adverse effect on model precision by requiring a large number of concept annotations to improve model precision or by causing the omission of some input information."
